# Kombo Manager — Architectural Rules

## Boundaries
- Only modify files inside wp-content/plugins/kombo-manager/
- Never touch theme files (kombo/ or kombo-child/)
- Never modify WooCommerce core or WC template files
- Extend WC via hooks/filters only

## Class structure
- Main class: KomboManager\KomboManager — singleton via get_instance()
- Activator: KomboManager\Activator — called only from register_activation_hook
- Deactivator: KomboManager\Deactivator — called only from register_deactivation_hook
- Autoloader: KomboManager\Autoloader — registered before anything else

## DB tables
- Created only in Activator::activate() — never on every page load
- Always check if table exists before CREATE TABLE
- Always use $wpdb->prefix . 'km_' prefix
- Always use dbDelta() for table creation

## Activity log
- Every manager action must write to {prefix}km_activity_log
- Log: user_id, manager_name, action_type, object_type, object_id, old_value (JSON), new_value (JSON), created_at
- No manager feature is complete without its log write

## Reference numbers
- Format: KM-XXXX where XXXX is zero-padded order ID
- Generated once on order creation — never regenerated
- Stored in order meta or km_orders table

## Admin CSS
- All admin styles scoped with .km-admin- prefix
- Never override WP core admin styles